frus:attachment.p:
The dispute between Brazil and Argentina over the territory of
                                Misiones (30,000 square kilometers) settled by the award of the
                                President of the United States;

The dispute between Argentine and Paraguay over the region between
                                the rivers Verde and Pilcomayo, settled by the award of the
                                President of the United States;

The dispute between Peru and Bolivia (over a territory as extensive
                                as the one claimed by Ecuador) settled by the award of the President
                                of Argentine;

The dispute between Venezuela and Great Britain over Guayana (100,000
                                square kilometers), settled by the award of an arbitration
                                tribunal;
